<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-03-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-08"><hi rend="italic">March 8,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that shippers have been advised in accordance with Mr.
                            Choate’s cablegram of the 7th instant.</p>
                        <p>Directs that British foreign office be advised that Norton &amp; Son
                            suggest the danger of long continued confinement below hatches of a
                            shipment of oil on the <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi>, resulting in
                            spontaneous combustion and destruction of ship and cargo.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>